title: Print, "Prestes de La Loy (The Nimble of Loy), plate 9 from Caravanne du Sultan à la Mecque (Caravan of a Sultan Going to Mecca),", 1748
inscribed: Inscribed across lower margin: Prestes de La Loy; J.V. del. Sc.
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of Eleanor G. Hewitt
description: Bearded man in Turkish costume sits in front of low wall, with legs crossed. His torso is turned so that he faces frontally, his hands at waist. He wears plumed turban, with strings of pearls looped on fronts.
